  "title": "fix(searchbox): SearchBox should not change the state if SearchOnEnterKeyPress",
  "body": "This patch revisits the previous solution to prevent impact on the URL Sync mechanism. It uses the `change` event again and impacts only the behaviour of the SearchBox.\r\n\r\nThe solution also contains a refactoring that introduces a default value for the queryHook which reduces the control flow complexity.\r\n\r\nStaging: http://opposite-girls.surge.sh/\r\n\r\nElements that you can check in the staging website:\r\n - see that the use of the second search box does not trigger an update of the URL\r\n - changing the filters creates new history steps, and you can go back and forth using the browser buttons\r\n\r\nfix #2105 #2117 ",
